The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Metro | The City Diary
                                                                                                               The City Diary
                State environment minister Sailen Sarkar on Wednesday announced financial support of Rs 50,000 for the Calcutta Municipal Corporation, Rs 20,000 for the Howrah Municipal Corporation and Rs 3,000 each for other municipalities in the Calcutta Metropolitan Area to help them clean the Hooghly after Puja immersions.    The state has sanctioned Rs 42 crore for building Kolkata Kala Kendra at Rawdon Square. PWD minister Kshiti Goswami said on Wednesday that the cultural centre would house an art gallery and a drama archive.    Mohammad Abid Khan, 32, and his cousin Injamul Haque, 8, were mowed down by a truck near the Dhulagarh truck terminal on Wednesday afternoon. Police said the duo, both residents of Domjur, were waiting on a bike when a fly ash-laden truck hit them from behind and sped away.    Asit Bandopadhyay and Ardhendu Das, in their mid-30s, were arrested by the CID on Wednesday in Bankura town for duping several youths in Calcutta and Bankura. Police said the accused are employees of Bankura Engineering College and had taken Rs 50,000 to Rs 1 lakh each from several people with the false promise of securing them jobs.    The high court on Wednesday refused to intervene in a matter pending before a trial court, as requested by the CMC. On July 24, 2009, the CMC had sent a notification to Dakshin Kolkata Sansad to shut down its bar-cum-restaurant at Deshapriya Park as it didnt have the necessary permission.																																																		   The club had moved a petition before Justice P.K. Deb, who issued an injunction on the notification till November 20.                                                                                                                                                                
